**Describe the bug**

* assertj core version: 3.25.0

Commit 498ee5bb0a5cc367420cdb3c8e0e93d6e4bf5e51 introduced a regression in `AbstractMapAssert.containsExactly`.

Specifically, it is not always safe to put `null` into a `Map`.

https://github.com/assertj/assertj/blob/887f97b65da068e03308a6373a0c8a76912377aa/assertj-core/src/main/java/org/assertj/core/internal/Maps.java#L589

**Test case reproducing the bug**

The following now fails with a `NullPointerException`.

```java
@Test
void assertJBug() {
	Properties properties = new Properties();
	properties.setProperty("k1", "v1");
	properties.setProperty("k2", "v2");
	assertThat(properties).containsExactly(entry("k1", "v1"), entry("k2", "v2"));
}
```
